    "body": "The libcpp_algo test with\r\n\r\n        make_heap(v.begin(), v.end(), greater)\r\n\r\ngenerates\r\n\r\n    /* \"libcpp_algo.pyx\":23\r\n *\r\n *     if reverse:\r\n *         make_heap(v.begin(), v.end(), greater)             # <<<<<<<<<<<<<<\r\n *         sort_heap(v.begin(), v.end(), greater)\r\n *     else:\r\n */\r\n    std::make_heap<std::vector<int> ::iterator,bool (int, int)>(__pyx_v_v.begin(), __pyx_v_v.end(), __pyx_f_11libcpp_algo_greater);\r\n\r\n\r\nbut the explicit template parameter for the compare function to make_heap has wrong type\r\nit should be\r\n\r\n   std::make_heap<std::vector<int>::iterator, bool (*) (int, int) >\r\n\r\nas otherwise the function argument doesn't decay.  Both GCC version 7 and clang++ with libc++\r\n(tested version 3.8) FAIL the testcase otherwise.\r\n\r\nIt works when auto-deducing the template parameter or when fixing its type.",
