            "body": "The C++ standard is clear, the `Compare` template argument must be a _function object type_, not a function type:\r\n\r\n[alg.sorting]:\r\n\r\n1. All the operations in 25.4 have two versions: one that takes a function object of type `Compare` and one that uses an `operator<`.\r\n\r\n2. `Compare` is a function object type (20.9). The return value of the function call operation applied to an object of type `Compare`, when contextually converted to `bool` (Clause 4), yields `true` if [...]\r\n\r\n`bool(*)(int, int)` is a function object type, but `bool(int,int)` is not.",
